                            <comment id="13914471" author="svenmeier" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 12:53:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Possible fix with yet another condition in WebPageRenderer&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13914488" author="dimarzio" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 13:24:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a workaround for the problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Extend RedirectPage -&amp;gt; anotate it with RequireHttps -&amp;gt; insert this page between source (http) and target (https) pages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The second redirect leads to the https page!&lt;/p&gt;

